---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Terms of Use | Belt Tuner">
  <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
  
  <h2>1. General Use</h2>
  <p>Belt Tuner is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind. Your use of the tool is at your own risk.</p>

  <h2>2. Hardware Safety</h2>
  <p><strong>Over-tensioning belts can severely damage your 3D printer's stepper motors, bearings, and frame.</strong> Always verify target frequencies with your printer manufacturer's official documentation before applying tension. We do not accept any liability for hardware damage resulting from the use of this tool.</p>

  <h2>3. Accuracy</h2>
  <p>While Belt Tuner uses mathematical algorithms to estimate audio frequency, background noise and hardware differences can affect accuracy. Always use your best judgment.</p>

  <style>
    h1, h2 {
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-top: var(--space-6);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    }
    p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    }
    strong {
      color: var(--color-warning);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
